<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Styling Text and Fonts</title>
  <style>
  font-family: sans-serif;
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1> p {
         text-shadow:
        1px 1px 1px red,
        2px 2px 2px red; 
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: bold; }
        Welcome to Text Styling</h1>
  </header>
  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>p {
        font-size: 2rem;
        font-weight: lighter;}
        Font Properties</h2>
      <p> p{
      text-align: justify;}
      This paragraph demonstrates the use of font-family, font-size, and font-weight properties.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Text Alignment</h2>
      <p> p {
      text-align: justify;}
      This paragraph demonstrates how to align text using the text-align property.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>text-transform: uppercase; Transforming Text</h2>
      <p> p {
      text-align: justify; 
      text-transform: capitalize; }
      This paragraph demonstrates text transformation with uppercase, lowercase, and capitalization.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Text Shadow</h2>
      <p> p {
       text-shadow:
     1px 1px 1px gray,
     2px 2px 2px gray;
      text-align: justify; }
      This paragraph demonstrates how to add shadow effects to text.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Lists</h2>
      <ul> {
        list-style-image: url("star.svg"); }
        <li>Item One</li>
        <li>Item Two</li>
        <li>Item Three</li>
      </ul>
      <ol> {
        list-style-type: upper-roman;

        <li>First Step</li>
        <li>Second Step</li>
        <li>Third Step</li> }
      </ol>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer>
  p { 
    text-align: center; }
    <p>Styling Text and Fonts Lab Â© 2025</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>